Hi all. Has anyone noticed weird behavior when editing a drag and drop page if `button:before` is used in a theme’s css files?
I placed the following code
```button:before, .button:before {
  transition: transform .3s ease-in-out, -webkit-transform .3s ease-in-out;
  position: absolute;
  top: 0;
  left: 0;
  right: 0;
  bottom: 0;
  content: "";
  z-index: -1;
  background: {{ button_bg_color }}; // this can be any color, doesn't have to be a variable
}```
in a theme’s `theme-overrides.css` file and it changes the HubSpot context menus. Is this correct behavior? Should my code affect the HubSpot CMS menus?
